\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid15685967 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Could you give your name and address please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You mean here? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 Gwen Mary Jones, Manod House, Llan Festiniog.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Are you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 When did you get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh I don't remember which year you know, it was - 19 - 1930 - oh I don't remember you know. I think it was 1934. Yes, that's right, 1934.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 In the year 1898. In Soly Mynydd, in Ffestiniog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh I didn't live very long in the house I was born in, because my mother and father moved to Trawsfynydd 
to Bryn Rhyd and I was there until I was eleven years old and then when I was eleven years old I came from there to Cae Iago. And then when I got married I went to Hafod Ysbytty. And then I went to Teiliaumawr and then I retired from farming and I came he
re. That was seven years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How many years were you living in Hafod Ysbytty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - it must have been about - twelve - twelve years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember why your family made the moves they did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well one thing was that my mother and father 
got a house near to my grandparents in Trawsfynydd. And this was with the butcher business, and my father used to help his father with the butcher business. And then the house }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 deteriorated}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  and the business }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 expanded}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  and my father came to Cae Iago with the m
eat business and he - he organised this with a - a horse and cart until he got a van.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well there were nine of us altogether. And I'm the oldest of them all. There are three girls and six boys.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember what order they came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh well I was the eldest. Then came Bob. Then Teddy. Then little Mary. Then Griffith Ellis, boy. And then Evan. And then - Mary Anwen. Then Howell and then John. John's the youngest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you know how many years there were between each of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Well - I was - twenty when the youngest one was born. There must have been, what, about two and a half years between us all, something like that anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - no I don't remember. No I've no idea, I can only remember when he died. He died when he was seventy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh it must have been twenty-six years ago. Oh he came from Doldinas in Cwn Prysor, a remote valley above Trawsf
ynydd. That's a very far place. And there wasn't a proper road leading up to the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh he was a butcher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Was that what he did all his life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, all his life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did he have a shop at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, no, he neve
r had a shop, he was just - he did the round with the horse and cart. And later on he got a van. And he had a cover over his cart and - you know, to cover the meat. And then of course he got the van. And my brother Teddy took over the business afterwards.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And that was the only job he had was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Yes. Oh no, wait a minute, he used to go round and help the farmers to kill the pigs, to castrate the lambs, and he killed beef. And the farmer might want a quarter or half that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you ever remember your father being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
No. Never. No, not a day out of work, he was very busy. He'd get up at four o'clock in the morning and go up to the mountain to castrate the lambs and things like that for people. No, he - he worked very hard all throu
gh his life. He was never out of work for a day. He'd go and - kill pigs for the farmers to be salted, you know, in those days. No, I mean, he was a - he was a - he was a - a good man.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well, if you'd asked me that last night I mean I could have told you, I could have looked it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 When did she die?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh she's been dead now for, what, twenty-two years. Twenty-two years since - last March.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How old was she when she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh seventy-three. Yes, that's - that's what she was when she died, she'd have been seventy-four in the June that year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Where was she from?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\tx2880\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid15685967 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh she came from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 Soly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  Mynydd. That's where she'd been born and bred. And - and what she did was to wo
rk on farms in the area at - Penbont.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid15685967 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
And that's what she did in her life before she got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, you know she went to - as a servant, she worked in the house in fact mostly. And - she cooked and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember how many different firms she went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, she - she went to lots of farms, I mean she went to Ysbytty - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 Haford}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  Ysbytty where my - husband was born and bred, she worked there. And then she went to Gyfynys for years and she went to Penbont for years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 she}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
 work after she got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. No. No, she had enough work with us, the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did she do any part time jobs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. No, not at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember how many rooms there were in the house which you lived in 'til you were eleven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
The one in Trawsfynydd you mean? Well there's a kitchen, a small parlour - two bedrooms and then - in the other half we kept peat and things like that. You know, the old - the old fashioned thing - way. And then we moved to Cae Iago. And tha
t was a - a pretty noble house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember how many rooms there were in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh there was a parlour, a kitchen, a small kitchen and a pantry and four bedrooms. But - now it's been redone and it's got three bedrooms and a bathroom upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Was there anyone else apart from your brothers and sisters and parents living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, no, no, no one other than the family, 'cos I mean there was a - whole crowd of children, there wasn't room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your mother pay anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
No, no, she didn't, I had to start working for her very young. I had to do a lot before I went to school. And that's what I did you know, I - I stayed at home and helped. I never went away to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no, you know washing, backing, everything was done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember your mother or father making or mending the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh my mother used to - mend everything. And she sewed a lot, made things. She made shirts for my father. And of course she }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 sewed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  everything for - for us - the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you usually have new clothes or secondhand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - no we had new clothes. My - grandfather, no, his - his children, they used to have - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 new clothes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  every y
ear. But - but we didn't have new clothes every year, but they were passed down from one to the other as - as the - we grew out of them. But you know we were never without best shoes. Shoes for going to chapel and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Was there a special time at which clothes were bought?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, I mean we'd have new clothes before the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 aman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
a, the chapel eistedfodd. That would be in May, because we always went to the Gamanfa in a white }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 frock,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
 a nice one. We were very grand at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your mother or father make or mend the family's shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh no, no, they were sent out to the cobbler. There were - there were cobblers in Trawsfynydd then who made, you know, all sorts of shoes. They made what we - what we call - home shoes, which are, you know, you don't - you don't get those now you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you ever have new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, yes, we were looked after with - with shoes. Yes, our feet were always all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your father help your mother with jobs around the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, he didn't, he didn't have time. He was too busy with his own work. And - and my mother was experienced in it anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 He didn't help her with the cooking or the washing or washing or washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did he do the fire for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 N
o he didn't, in fact my father was very bad at - helping in the house. His experience was outside, he hadn't - he had no experience of inside work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about decorating and repairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh my mother did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Well - in those days people would go round and - mend - mend the roofs you know before the winter. Yes, that's how it was, there were plenty of men available to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your father dress or undress you or bath you or read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh 
no he didn't, he wanted peace to do - to get on with his work. No, my mother did that sort of thing, and then because we were a crowd together we used to help each other. No, my - my father did very little.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
No, he didn't. In fact we very rarely went out, we - once a year maybe we had a trip or something. A Sunday school trip to Rhyl or somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about the times when your mother went out, did your father look after you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, y
es, he'd baby sit, he'd do that. Yes, on a Sunday night or something. When my mother went to chapel, oh yes, he was very good like that. I mean, but he wasn't the sort of person who'd get the supper ready or - or anything like that you know. My mother did
 that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you have any jobs that you had to carry out regularly at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh yes. Yes I had to work. I used to - you know, even - when I was at school - I had to look after the children, feed them, see that they were having enough breakfast and I
 used to have to wash the front step. I can remember the floor. It was a slate floor, I can remember it now, a - a big slate and a little and a littler one. And I used to have to wash the - the doorsteps every morning before I went to school, whatever the
 weather. And I had to run to do - the shopping, fetch messages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And you carried on doing this after you left school too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, I mean I used to - I helped my mother for years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about your brothers and sisters, did they help around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well - no, I mean, my father wanted the boys - to go away and learn a craft, become - to become butchers. He wanted the boys to learn. He -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And that's what they did was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, yes, that's - Teddy did that. Of course, Bob, he wasn
't very strong and he died when he was sixteen, he was the one nearest to me. And Teddy went to Llandudno, to learn to be a butcher. And then Griffith left school at fourteen and - went away again to learn to be a butcher. And then my brother Evan, he wen
t next. We've just buried him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 When they were at home before they went away to study did they help around the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, yes, they had to, they had to. My brother and me, we used to go and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 fetched}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  the coal from the station, and we used to have to take the meat into Trawfynydd. Oh - no, they - they had to work. But of course I mean they - they were 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 mischievous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
 as well. I mean I remember my brother and a friend of his riding on the back of a pig and running this poor pig until it was nearly dead. And he a good thrashing for that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember if the older children helped the younger children with things that they found difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, yes, I did - we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did the younger ones help the older ones at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no, very lit
tle - very little. The younger children were allowed to play and things. Yes, they were allowed to play, in fact they got every advantage, particularly Mary and Even and Howell and John. Mary Anwyn that was. They were given every opportunity to go to scho
ol. Only I had to leave when I was fourteen years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
 expect you to go to bed at any particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, yes, we had to go bed. We had to go early. And in the winter we didn't have even a candle to go up to bed. We had to go up in 
the darkness. We couldn't read or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Who put you to bed? Your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, yes, she did. But we had to go by ourselves as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember how old you were when you first went to bed on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh I used to go when I 
was very young you know. And there was a crowd of us so, you know, we used to go together. And I remember after we came to live in Cae Iago - Howell and John would be going to bed and I remember one of used to have to go up with him, I think it was John, 
u
ntil he slept that was. And - you know, what we wanted to do was to go out and play ball and - and things like that, and so we have to put a bolster down alongside John in order to persuade them that we were still there in bed with him. Oh yes, I can reme
mber, you know, wanting to go out to play and we had to be in bed - with - with the younger ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you share your bedroom with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, yes, I did, I used to share it with one sister. And we'd share with the boys if a - a stranger came 
to stay or something. Only of course we were very young then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And you only had two bedrooms in the old house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, that was in the old house though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What was the arrangement there, the children in one and your mother and father in the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, that's right, that's what it was like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Which room did you have a bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - you know, by the fire in a tub. Every Saturday we had it. And of course we had to wash in the mornings on weekdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about having clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - every week we had those. Unless of course you had an accident or something and had to have - clean clothes some other time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Where did the family eat their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh in the kitchen. At the table. And on Saturdays my mother and me wou
ld have our meal at the round table, 'cos there wasn't - room for everybody to sit at the round table, but - after the little ones had gone to bed and my father came in late on Saturdays from the meat round, so we used - my mother and me used to sit at th
e - round table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room? Did you eat in the parlour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 No,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  no, always in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Where did your mother cook, in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What did she cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh she
 had a - a grate and an oven. And she'd bake things in the oven and fry things on the fire. And she'd boil up the clothes in a saucepan, you know, those big saucepans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What time did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well, you know, we had to be at school by nine so - oh we had breakfast about half past eight - half past seven to eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were all the family there for breakfast?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well I'm sure we used to come down one by one - to breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Didn't your father go out to work earlier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, of course he - he got up earlier to go out and slaughter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 your mother got up with him to make him breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, yes, she did, always. Before he went out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What did you usually have to eat or drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - we'd have tea to drink and before that we had to have gruel or - soup - or - bruas, oat bread and beef - beef broth. Or shot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you ever have anything special for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
 don't think so, but we used to have those alternate days, the things I talked about. Or we might have a - a treacle - butty or - or an egg or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - well we used to take our food with us to school. You know, we'd take bread - bread and milk in - in tins. Or sandwiches or something. 
And we'd have dinner when we came back in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh he had dinner - at - midday and he - he also had a dinner in the evening. He was very fond of - meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you always have meat for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, every night we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about Sunday, did you have a special dinner then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, we had a special one then. 'Cos everyone was home on Sunday for lunch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What did you usually have for supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well on Sunday we had - cold meat from - from -
 you know, the roast we had at lunchtime. And we'd have cold meat sandwiches. And we'd have tea and tinned pears or something sometimes, and jam and cheese.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about supper during the week?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh we had to have - porridge and things. And a cup of tea or whatever it was we wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You said your mother baked her own bread, did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes. Yes she did everything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did she bottle fruit and vegetables or make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no, she didn't - you know, we weren't very fond of those sort of things. But she made plenty of jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about making wine or medicines of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no, she didn't. Not really until we came to Cae Iago to live.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did she make beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh goodness me, no. I mean, we didn't know how to make it and we didn't have any money to get the things to make it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your mother or father grow their own fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, they did. I mean, we used to grow potatoes and carrots and things like that, and swedes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did they buy any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, they did, they had to. Because we were such a large family you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember having fruit or vegetables that were dried or tinned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your parents or family keep any animals at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well - yo
u see, we lived near the farm where my grandfather was. And my grandfather was a farmer you see, and he kept the animals and he used to milk. I can remember going to milk when I was a very little girl. I'd have a quart tin in my hand. And we had this old 
cow called - called Dolgeltha.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 But your father didn't work on the farm at all did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No he didn't, except just at haymaking time. No, he was out all the time with the horse and cart, selling meat you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How many times a week would you say you had meat to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh well I'd say we had it - nearly every day. I mean we might have a lump of - ox liver boiled - mixed in with red cabbage and potatoes and - in a sort of stock. And we'd have a little bit of meat of some sort you know, I mean
 we were all very fond of meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you ever have tinned meat as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
No. No, never. No, I didn't even know what something like corned beef was. We only had tinned salmon. And we wouldn't have liked it either. We wouldn't have eaten it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember having extra meat like rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, we used to have rabbit, but nobody liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How did you come by these rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well, the farmers would catch them in traps you see. And we'd get one like that. But we didn't like them at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You didn't get them regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you ever remember seeing your mother getting less food in order that her family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. No I don't think so. I don't think I saw any of that. But if 
- if somebody arrived at mealtimes of course she'd take some from somebody to give to them. But mainly that was from the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your father have more food ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, I don't think so, just the same as we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were you allowed to talk at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, we weren't allowed to talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were you allowed to choose what you wanted to eat out of what had been cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. No, we couldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You had to eat everything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, whatever was on the table we had to eat or starve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What did your parents say if you left food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh they got very angry about that, you know, if you left food - spare as it were. And I remember my father right 'til the end of his life, you know, he'd pick up any crumbs that w
ere around and I can remember him, you know, doing like this, picking up the crumbs and putting them in his mouth, and that - that way he said that none of us would ever - be in want of anything. And a lot of people remember him doing that you know, peopl
e of that generation. Picking up the crumbs. He was frightened of leaving even a single crumb behind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 If there was something on the table that you wanted did you have to wait until somebody offered it to you or could you ask for it directly?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh w
ell yes, you could ask - ask someone to pass it to you. But - that was, you know, if - if they'd finished with it, if the older ones had finished - using it. because the younger ones got everything afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 There was a definite order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, it always went from the oldest to the youngest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were you allowed to ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, if you hadn't had enough. And sometimes we'd get it and sometimes we wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did they expect you to hold your knife and fork in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, I mean they expected you to hold your knife in your right hand. And we had to eat tidily.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about sitting in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, yes, we did. Not to put our elbows on the table or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were you allowed to bring toys or books to the table during a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no. No, not - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were you allowed to leave the table when you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, we couldn't, we had to wait - for everyone else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did the whole family sit down at the table at mealtimes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, yes, if everyone was at home. Yes, everyone did. - We all had our food together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 On the same table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, everyone had his place. And everyone had their own chair too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your mother serve the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What order was it served in? Your father first and then from the eldest to the youngest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, that's right, yes. And we had to wait our turn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember where your younger brothers and sisters sat before they were old enough to feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh they - they'd sit in a - on a chair, a special chair and - the older ones would - teach them to - feed. And feed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 So they'd sit up next to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, that's right. You see, they'd - they might sit on a chair next to me, a proper chair and learn, you know, like to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 coppy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  the adults. But if they were sitting in the high - in the - the small chair, the baby chair, then I'd have to go over to them and feed them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember how old they were when they joined in with the family at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh I don't know, every age. About - oh from three - upwards I'd say. Until they were, you know, old enough to sit up at the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Would you say your mother was an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did she show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes. She was very quiet.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 If you were worried about something could you share your worries with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, yes, of course, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh - well he was stricter than my mother, but - he was very kind too. But he did have a violent temper. He'd forget you see. Only - my mother, you know, kept her crossness inside her. She never showed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your father show affection to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you share your worries with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh yes, everything. You know, we - we - talked and helped each other, everything. You know, we'd do things like - helping take his - clothes off or - take his coat off. Anything, you know, the old fashioned way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh they expected us to be totally obedient to them. If they said something we had to do it that minute. We couldn't wait - there was - we had to. That minute.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How would you say your parents brought you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh, to be friendly towards each other and to share everything. Yes, we had to share everything, and we had to help them, if they needed help with anything. I mean,
 help at school or anything like that. And as I was the eldest I had to look after them at school, and if I saw them being mischievous at school I had to bring them home. You know, in the middle of school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 If a strange child hit you were you encouraged to hit him back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh yes, we'd been taught to do that. If someone was cross with you when you had to be cross back. No, we weren't given any sort of - in a way softness, you know, we had to fight our way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What kind of people do you think that your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 They hoped that we'd be - hardworking. Honest and hardworking. And to help others. Yes, we had to help other people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Is this what your parents felt to be important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, yes, these were th
e things that were important in life. Being honest and telling the truth. We'd get - a row if we didn't tell the truth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were you allowed to swear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no. No, we used to have a row if we heard - were heard swearing. But that was only if they hear
d us of course. Of course I could tell you more things - other things about when we came to live in Cae Iago. You want that later on I suppose do you? I mean there you know we couldn't even bring a duster out to dust on Sunday. We couldn't clean our shoes
. We couldn't touch the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 shoe brush}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
 at all and we couldn't read a newspaper. And when we grew up and realized that we ought to read and things like that, well - my father used to go to sleep on a Sunday afternoon and then we'd go like mice to read the newspa
per. And if we had to clean our shoes - you know, we wanted to go somewhere on Monday or something, well we would. But apart from that I mean we had to - oil our shoes with this horrible black sort of oil on a Saturday night, everything had to be done on 
the - the Saturday night after we'd had a bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 If adults were talking were you allowed to join in with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no. Not at all. Because, you know, they'd often send us to bed when - visitors come round. They'd send us to bed straight away. And -
 you know, we'd get up to tricks, we'd come up to the top of the stairs to listen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well - they'd be angry at that and afterwards you know, we'd go up to them and say - laugh mother, laugh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How were you punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh we were punished quite a bit. We'd get, you know, the birch rod.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How often did you get the birch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well, you know, if we'd - done something really bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 From your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, from both of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember a particular occasion on which you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
But I can't actually remember me being punished, I was really quiet, but the boys were always copping it, they were much worse. And they'd get a really terrible row and punishment if they were bad.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What sort of things did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh throwing stones. And refusing to listen. Sowing the hayfield or something like that. 'Cos there we had to work and do what they said. 'Cos there was a way of do
ing things you know and we had to obey under those circumstances. We couldn't say no. And if they did they were punished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How did you feel towards being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh we were frightened. Oh yes, we were frightened of being punished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Would yo
u say that you received the ideas that you had about how to behave from your mother and your father or would you say that one was more }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 influential}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  than the other
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 I don't think so, because - the family was really like a chain, any everyone was linked to everybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 So you'd say that both of them had an affect on you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Yes. We were all very friendly. Oh and sometimes - you know, there'd be a fight in the family, a quarrel, but we've been brought up on the whole to - you know - behave prope
rly. And behave properly towards everyone. I mean, other people outside the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 But would you say that both your mother and father gave you the ideas that you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, I mean we had to. We had to do what they said. Or there was trouble.
 We had to listen to what they said, and we weren't allowed to go anywhere either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about birthdays, was it different to any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. I mean I - I never had anything. No, I don't think so, I don't remember any of us having anything exc
ept my sister of course on her twenty-first birthday. She had a lot. She had a party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 But you don't remember when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. No. No, nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about Christmas Day, did you remember doing anything with your mother and father on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - nothing much, except that we always had a goose and plum pudding. We had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 plenty}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  of that, but other things - well we just didn't have them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about musical instruments, did you have any of those in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
No, nothing at all. Work was everything - as far as they were concerned. It was all work. I mean, I wanted to go on with school but I had to come home - when I was fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about singing, did anyone sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, they were hopeless. Really terrible. Nobody could sing. Only I'd like to try in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 eisteddfod}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 . I'd do recitation. And the other thing I used to like doing was writing compositions, essays. I loved doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And then you'd compete with those compositions would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, t
hat's right. Another thing I used to like to do was learning chapters from the Bible. And - recite them, you know - in a - in a competitive way. I used to like doing lots of those sort of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 So you never had any musical evenings or anything at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your parents play games with - you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were there any books in your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Very few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about newspapers, did you get those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 We had very few newspapers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. No we didn't have anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you ever remember seeing your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, my father did read the newspaper, but my - mother hardly read at all. Only - my father only read the newspaper. They never read books.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember them reading aloud at all, to each other or to you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Well I'll tell you what, I mean - we - in the evening we used to have sort of composition - competitions to see who could say verses and things from the Bible, but apa
rt from that there was nothing. I mean, you know, it was a time when - there was no interests - there were no interests - that we might have - had that - meant that we had to read. But anyway we used to go to the Band of Hope and the Seate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember a funeral in the family at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh yes, I do, I remember a funeral. 'Cos when I - I remember the one - when - we lost - my youngest sister, at Christmas, and I remember us burying her and I remember burying my brother afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember who went to the funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, I did, my mother and father and me. The older ones went. And somebody came to babysit the younger children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 When you said there were nine children in the family you did count those two that died in the nine didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes. Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you war mourning clothes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes. Black clothes, everything was black.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember people wearing black armbands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, they did, if they had light }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 colored}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  coats they had to wear a black armband. And the men would wear black bands round their hats as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you go visiting friends, relatives and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, we used to go for - visiting - relatives. And we were allowed to go and visit our friends, you know, afte
r we'd grown up a bit. I remember when we were living in Traws I used to go and spend Sunday with a - a friend of mine. And goodness me, we got - I got such a welcome. We'd get a special tea. They had some sort of special tea, I wonder what it was called.
 
- Anyway they used to have to give me nectar tea because I didn't like the taste of the tea that they had. China tea, that's what it was. I didn't like China tea, so it had to be another pot of tea for me. And you'd get - bacon and brawn, we'd really get 
a fantastic welcome. And then maybe a - a couple of - two or three friend's would come to live with - to - to see us in Bryn Rhyd, we didn't have anything to play with, just the - branches of the trees. And so we used to - see who was best at those.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you go with your mother and father to visit friends and relatives?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, we did, but usually with my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you go shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, we did. We used to go - had to fetch messages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you go shopping with your mother ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 O
h very rarely, usually we had to go on our own. And then, you know, at the end of the week my father would bring back the shopping in the cart. My mother would give him a list for him to bring back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you go out with your father alone at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, very little. No, he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 too busy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 , he couldn't really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember going on any trips or outings with your parents at all, Bank Holidays and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, yes, we did as we got older. We - had very good trips to the chapel, that was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 Babel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
 Sunday school, and we'd go all the time and we'd go to different places and once I remember three charabancs going. Everybody went. They joined in to go on the trip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Where did you usually go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well we went to Rhyl, to Chester, to Aberystwyth. We had really very good trips.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you ever go away on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh very little when I was small.- Until I got, you know, older. No, I went very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You don't remember a particular occasion on which you went on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 I remember us going to Duffryn - to see my mother's brother. And I went there with my cousin as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How long did you go for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh I went for a week, but I was very homesick, I wanted to come home. I remember, you know, one time when I was there by mysel
f and - my Uncle John asked me, when he saw me crying, what was the - what's the matter? And I said, I'm homesick, I want my mother. And he said, well look at me, I'm just the same as your mother. And I said to him, no, you're not half as pretty as my mot
her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You were alone this time were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, I - I was, you know, we'd been allowed - I'd been allowed to go for - for a holiday you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember what sort of things you did on this holiday, apart from crying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh not very much really. We'd go to the seaside at Dyffryn. But then the seaside was, you know, at least a mile from - from where we were.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Could you tell me how you spent your Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh, we were very busy on Saturdays. I had to clean, I had to black the grate. Had to wash the floor. Everything happened on Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you play at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Very little, except when - friends came - my friends came to stay with us, when we were on holiday. And then I had to scrub the floor. And then in the
 evening I had to bath the little children, and clean the shoes - ready for Sunday. No, we didn't do very much - playing on Saturday. And another thing we had to do was - take meat round to people. I can remember going for miles, taking meat to people, af
ter we came to live in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146  Cae}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  Iago. Yes, we used to walk up as far as Bont Yr Afon Gam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You went all that way on your own without your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes we did. You know, we walked. First we'd go to Tyddyn Bach, and then we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 cross}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  the river and sometimes the river'd be too full, then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 there\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  be a lot of crying 'cos we couldn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 cross}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
 over the river. So we'd have to go up to the own and cross two - two bridges before we could get over to Tyddynbach, and then we'd go up that big hill, and up to Bont Yr Afon
 Gam. And I remember us once going from Bont Yr Afon Gam to Llyn Morwynion, to the old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 armoury,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
 and - I remember that Mrs Pritchard from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 Au Olen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
 who used to live up there took her name - her pen name from that and became the guardian of cwnbach, which is the valley below.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How did you spend Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well we had to go to chapel three times. But sometimes we'd have to babysit, alternately. In the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you wear different clothes on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, we wore - our best clothes. Best
 Sunday clothes. And when we lived in Traws I remember going with Mr and Mrs Roberts from Cod Cae Du and they were very religious. And they'd go with a horse and cart and I can remember sitting in the middle between them and I was very proud of myself and
 of course - as I'd gone with them. Riding along in the cart.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You've already said you couldn't play or work on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes. No, we couldn't do anything on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 This was because your parents thought it was wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, that's right. It was to do with respect, respecting the Sabbath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You said your parents went to chapel, what denomination was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh Methodist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your mother and father go three times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no, they couldn't do that. They used to send us to Sunday s
chool and then we'd babysit in the evening alternately and if I stayed home then my mother and father would go. And another time my mother'd stay and me and my father would go, and then we used to have to say a verse from the Bible on Sunday - evening, in
 the chapel that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And you went on the Sunday school trips?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, we used to go on very good trips there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about other activities organized by the chapel, you've already mentioned the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, we used to go to the Ban
d of Hope, and to the Seate and of course I'd have to learn a verse. And we'd - we'd have to have - listen to the sermon on Sunday and - grasped the ideas behind it and explain these ideas in the seate. And then other people would ask questions, and thing
s like that. And I was still a member of the - reading meeting, which was a very interesting meeting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you ever belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. I didn't. Except for when there was an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 eisteddfod}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  in - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 Babel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  chapel, you know, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 local}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  chapel, and then I used to sing in the choir. No, you se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 , we weren't singers. We weren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Was there a temperance club connected with the chapel at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, there was. Temperance. High - in Highgate, Trawsfynydd. It's now the Co-op, but it used to be the temper
ance chouse. Everyone respected it tremendously because - it was something democratic in that - everybody contributed to doing it up, and making it into something and - if visiting - preachers came from somewhere, well then of course we'd go to Highgate a
nd have you know - cup of tea or something.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were you a member of this temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, we weren't, but my grandfather was. He was the most that way. That's my father's father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember any other clubs organized by the chapel at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
No, I don't think so, not in those days. There were only the things that I've already mentioned. There'd be - you know - sort of teas and things where you went to - to have tea with friends. But there were no sort of - other clubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember if you said grace before meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Yes, we did. We did it in turn. We had to learn different - sort of prayers in a way. We had to learn - give mother - and their forforgodd. And then there was another - another one which is in the form of a - qu
ite a big book. There was three altogether and we had to learn them all. But of course they've gone now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you say prayers before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, every time, and if we didn't we'd get a row.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no, we didn't do that, but they did that in my friend's house. They did that in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your father take any interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No he didn't really, except that he was a Liberal all his life. But not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you know why he was a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well I don't know, there wasn't really anything else was there, and also he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13265768\charrsid401146 very much}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  in aw}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
 of the Member of Parliament, Haydn Jones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - she was very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 uninterested in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember your mother or father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh well, they'd go every time to - to - to vote. I mean, they felt they were allowed to do that, that was their right. Only there - there wasn't any fuss. None at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And they always voted for the Liberals did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
In some areas at that time men felt that they might lose their jobs or their houses by voting differently from their employers, do you remember ever feeling that your father was under this sort of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Well no, because obviously he had his own business, and so he couldn't come under that sort of pressure. Only I remember that there were incidents of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You actually remember some do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes I do. I mean if the employer 
said something then you had to obey him. And I remember - I remember particularly the estate of Mr Wood and a lot of people from his estate were members of the - church too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And they had to vote Tory did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, they did. I mean, those sort o
f people did exist and - and you had to. In fact you had to against your beliefs - in order to - to live, for your livelihood. Otherwise you wouldn't be allowed to stay on the farm or whatever it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Your father wasn't a member of a political party was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no. No, he was - hardly interested in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 politics}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And they never worked for the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no. No, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Your mother didn't either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were your parents weren't working how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - by sewing and knitting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about your father, did he read the newspaper mainly?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, he read - he read very little, most of the time he slept, because he was tired out after working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your mother have any interests outside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, very few. Very few, because there weren't any in those days. It was just a question of bed and work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 She didn't go out to enjoy herself or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. Except with her sisters sometimes, she'd go and visit other sisters. But nothing else. She didn't belong to any society or anything.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What time did your father get home in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh, sometimes it would be very late. It depended what season of the year it was. When the farmers wanted to castrate
 the lambs or shear it or something then he'd be very late. And then on a Friday he'd get up at four o'clock in the morning to slaughter - slaughter sheep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did he kill the sheep himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, there was a slaughter house in - Trawsfynydd and in Cae Iago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did the farmers from around bring their sheep to him to be slaughtered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Yes, they did, I mean, he - you know - they - they sold them to him, and - the farmers'd bring the sheep to him and - he'd get up, as I said, at four o'clock in the
 morning, in summer that is, when the weather was bad. And then in - pig slaughtering season he'd be very busy. You know, it was work in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 He didn't go out in the evenings at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 He didn't ever go to clubs or pubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, he never did that, he never went into a pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Your mother neither?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, she didn't either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your father take part in any sports at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 He didn't go to the races or bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, not at all. No, nothing
 like that. But it was a very - happy life. They didn't know about anything except the - the small little world in which they lived. And it was a - a happy world. They only had their work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your mother or father belong to a savings club at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. But if we ever had any money then we had to take it to the Post Office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You didn't have any savings towards when you were sick, towards a funeral or towards buying boots or shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. As far as I remember we didn't. No, all we did was - s
ave in the Post Office if there was any spare money. And of course we paid everybody. And you - because the farmers would want money when they bought the sheep and the cows to the slaughter house, so then we'd have to pay out money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - champion. I got on with them all very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were you particularly close to any one of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, we were all close. My sister was the one that used to fight with the boys. No, I didn't ever fight with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 When you were a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh we played with each other. I remember an old lady - the things was we were over fond of playing little house when we were children and - you know, we'd have everything, crockery and - but I ne
ver had a doll. I only had a wooden one, which used to have a red face, but after I'd washed it so much that went. I never had a dolly. And I used to have this little house, and it was sort of in the back on a sort of - cliff place, rock - rock place. And
 the thing was, this old lady came to see us and she asked, where's the little house? And the thing was she wanted to go to the lavatory, but you know - I mean, what I did was to show her my little house. I mean, I had no idea what she was talking about.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you play with your neighbours at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Yes, and sometimes children used to come over but very little because - everybody had to stay at home and work. But I remember going over to a neighbouring farm and fetching the boys from there to take them to school. For the first time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 When you did play where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh we used to play when we were at school, in the playtimes that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 But when you played at home where was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh in the fields and around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What sort of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh we used to play rounders, in school that is. Yes. And played with tops. I used to like playing. And we used to play ball.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What sort of games did you play at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh you know, climbing trees and things. And then we used to collect wood - for the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well I mean you did that without noticing. But if you got dirty and tore your clothes then you had a row.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were you free to play with whoever you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes. Oh there was no difference made between anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Your parents didn't disapprove of you playing with anyone then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no. No, everyone was the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you ever belong to any youth organization?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, I never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How did you spend your free time, did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well, I did - I mean, what age do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Up 'til the time you left school, did you have any pets, did you collect anything, did you do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, I didn't like doing the gardening, I used to like being at it, you know, doing the milking. And when they were cutting the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 oats}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
 - my - grandfather would - you know, want us to gather up the bits they left behind, you know, with a rake. You know, the fine oats - to give to the little calves
 in the winter. Because you see I had so little time to play, me that is. I didn't really have any hobbies, except knitting. I used to knit socks when I was very small.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about going fishing or walking or on a bike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, I did it - very little. Again it - that was me you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you take part in any sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Yes. Yes I remember running once in a race when we had a - Sunday school picnic. And I remember us running. But that's the only time I remember. It was up at Tomen Yr -Mur you know. It's an old Roman fort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember going to theatres or concerts or music hall at all before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, very little. No, it was after I left school that I was able to go to Llandudno.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about the pictures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
No. We didn't. 'Cos I mean we had to walk wherever we wanted to go. And there was nothing for us then in those days. And they didn't have any time to take you somewhere and bring you back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your parents give you pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, we used to get money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How much did you get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh - we used to get very little. And I remember after - I left school I used to get the money from the eggs from father. But I used to have to buy my own clothes out of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 That was after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, that's right, after I left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Before you left school did you have pocket money regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And we used to have to save that, we had to take them to the Post Office, we couldn't spent them - it. And then visitors'd come
 round and you'd get a little bit of money from - someone. But we had to save it and take it - save it and take it to the Post Office.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did anyone come in to help your mother with the house, any relatives, friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, very little.
 But remember everybody was - very kind. Overwhelmingly kind, but I mean, they came - they didn't come to work for my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 If your mother was ill or had to stay in bed how did you manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh, I'd have to look after my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Even when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, oh yes. Oh yes, I'd have to look after her, and I'd have to do all the food and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember what happened when your younger brothers and sisters were born? How did you manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well, the doctor would c
ome at birth, and then - there would be a lady - my grandmother in fact used to come, to attend to my mother. And then after I came back from school then I'd do it. And I'd do everything that was necessary. But }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 otherwise}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  it was my grandmother, and my mothe
r would be in bed for a week. And she'd only have tea and toast for that week. That was at the time of the birth of every one of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you have any relatives living nearby? You've already said your grandfather and grandmother lived near.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, they used to live next - they were neighbours - next to us, that was for years, until I was eleven in fact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How much did you see of your grandparents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh I used to see a lot of them, yes. And my aunts too. And we were very friendly with my fa
ther's brother, Uncle Edwards he was - we called him. And we used to be allowed to go to - the stable in our }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 nightdresses}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
 and watch - him giving the horses their supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your parents have a lot of friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, they did. As far as I remember they were friends with everyone. You know, with the farmers, everyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Where did they see their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - well they'd call round. And some would call very often. And then of course my - father would go round with the meat and then of cou
rse - he'd talk to people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your parents share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, yes, they had - they had the same friends. Everyone was together. Everyone was the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your mother have her own friends at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, particularly with the Sunday school class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did she go and see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, you know, when something was on. It was very neighbourly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your father have his own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, he did too. Everything was very neighbourly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You said friends were invited to your house, how often did they come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well, they wouldn't come very often, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 because}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  everyone was too busy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 If they did come were they offered something to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes. Tea - and - cheese or - or meat if there was meat. And a cake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did they come on any special day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - yes, sometimes they did. They used - they tended to come on a Wednesday or a Thursday, if they came on a special day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Would you say that the friends that were invited were your mother's friends, your father's friends or friends of both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh there'd be a mixture coming. Friends of mother's and father's. and relatives as well. A lot of relatives would come - in those days.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did any friends come without invitations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes. Yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And neighbours too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your parents go visiting neighbours and friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well - no, because they didn't go - just to visit. They used to go if there was a specific message to take to somebody. If you had to take
 a message then of course we had to go. I remember a very old man who used to live in Tyddol, you know, down by the river, and he came to Bryn Rhyd to see us. He said - good children, tell their message straight away. And he always used to say his message
 
immediately. And my mother and father used to warn us that we had to - you know - give our message as soon as we went into the house. Don't - you know, stand around and chat and - pass the time before giving the message. And I still remember it, you know,
 
I've remembered it all the time. Yes, it's funny 'cos most people in this area spend a lot of time getting to the point you know, they won't - they won't say their message immediately. Oh yes, and they were terrible long ago you know. They'd never say the
ir message, you'd have to ask for it, ask what they wanted. And this old man, and he was so old you know, he said to us, good children - say their message immediately. And, you know, we accepted this and stuck to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 People tell us that in those days p
eople made their own amusements, do you remember your parents getting together with friends and neighbours to amuse themselves, to make music or play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, very little. Oh we did that very little. Because none of us could sing. But my parents, t
hey used to sort of talk - and tell stories and histories of places. Tell some story of the sale, about animals, animals they had. But there was very little of - anything like games. But I do remember that - my grandfather - used to like playing ludo and 
he'd play ludo all through the winter, even when there was a visitor there, and one evening my father went over there and my father asked my grandfather }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 questions}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  you know, but he wouldn't answer. He was too busy with his game. And my father got - angry at 
this, and consequently he - went against all games. He was angry at all games. 'Cos you see my grandfather was too keen on this ludo game. And of course we couldn't play after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 A lot of people divide society up into different classes or groups, w
ould you say that in the period before 1918 that you felt that some people belonged to one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 group}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  and some people to another?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, I wouldn't say that. Because everyone was with the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You don't remember feeling that some people were big nobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 There were big people in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh yes, there were a lot of big people. And you looked up to them too. And they lived a very different life from us, with - you know, more style in their food and things, everything like
 that. They had more - reason for being like that, because some - I mean that was in their nature in some of their nature. They were born to it. And therefore they had to carry this on. And then of course they had their own friends.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember feeling there was another class or classes, a middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - most people were farmers and - they sort of collected together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you feel that they were different from the ordinary workers, or did they differentiate themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no, I
 wouldn't say they made any distinction at all. Oh, not at all, but they had their own interests you see, they're interested in animals and - things, and the quarrymen were interested in the quarry and slates and things. You see, they had had schooling li
ke they had - have today, and so they didn't know about anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Which group would you say you belonged to? With the farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, except - I mean we - were really with the butchers, that's what I like being - that's who I like being with. And i
n a way because I had to - I had to be with the animals. I used to like being }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  the animals, like looking after them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What sort of people belonged to the same group as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh people who were very keen on their work and who enjoyed their work
. Because people used to like work in those days, everybody did, and they used to work to - work in - long hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What were the big people like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well you'd look up to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What sort of people were the big people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well we - you loo
ked up to them and you were frightened. You were afraid to mix with them too much, and they wouldn't mix either. They'd only give you a message and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 What about}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  the quarrymen, what sort of people were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh they were very good peop
le. And they were very - social - sociable. They were very experience in being in a community. They were very - communal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember being brought up to respect some people differently from others?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, we had to respect our Sunday scho
olteacher. And we thought the world of her. And we had to listen and learn what she said and then to the headmaster, we had to bow to him, and we were frightened to. And the policeman, we were frightened of him too. And I'm still frightened of policemen. 
And we were frightened of the policeman - even though we hadn't done anything wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You said you had to bow to some people, did the boys have to touch their caps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 To }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 whom}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
 did you do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh to the headmaster. And I'll tell you w
ho else we didn't dare - go against or do anything in the eyes of, and that was the leaders of the chapel and the minister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you have to bow or touch your cap to the big people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no, we didn't, not to them. Because they weren't really - in our area. We just left them alone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you ever remember calling anyone sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
No, not when I was small. But I mean, I remember after I married - after I grew up, I used to know Sir Lewis Casson and Sybil Thorndike and they'd com
e to tea with us. Because you see, after we married - they owned Hafod Ysbytty. They - it belonged to them and we were great friends with them - with Dame Sybil and Sir Lewis Casson. They were very kind to us, because I remember once - we had enormous }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 snowstorms}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
, enormous drifts - and we lost a - a lot of sheep and they offered us a lot of things. They were just more than kind to us. Beyond kindness
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 This was all after you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, that's right. And I think those were the only ones that I eve
r remember calling sir, madam. And I remember going to see Sybil Thorndike when she acted in Blauenau Ffestiniog, and I remember going there to see her acting. But I didn't understand very much of it. But we talked to her afterwards, they were people who 
were very close to you, and the children too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you ever remember anyone saying sir to your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no. No. No, they were very plain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Who was considered important in your area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well, you know, as I said - the -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You mean the chapel leaders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes. And the minister, and the headmaster and all the teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you come into contact with these people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, we did. Specially as we got older. We got a lot of our, you know, teaching from them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you know why they were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well it was their - rank, their status. And they taught the - the children to respect status, and to obey them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Who would you say the shopkeepers mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well, they had to mix with everyone. Becau
se there weren't many people so they couldn't afford to alienate customers. They were glad to get everyone to buy from them. Children and everything. They were pleased to see anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about the minister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh he'd come and visit us very often, and then we had to be very good children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Who did the teachers mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh they'd mix with everyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about the farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes - they'd mix with everyone too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did they stick to themselves at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, they didn't - th
ey did a long time ago though, because say - one farmer, you know, needed some money. Well - the - a neighbouring farmer would throw his purse over the river to the one that needed the money. You know, they looked after each other, and they were - excepti
onally that way inclined. If anyone was in trouble they'd help out. They were particularly like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Who did the employers mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - well they - they were - on their own. The farm labourers that is. And they had their freedom and could do -
 on a Saturday night, and could do what they liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You mean the farm labourers could?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Yes, the farm labourers, and the sons as well. And a lot of them would be courting and things. And then there'd be quoit playing, they'd do that, and they used to like that very much. They'd spend hours of time playing quoits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about employers like the employers in the quarry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh you mean the quarrymen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 The people who employed the quarrymen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, they - they thought of themselves a
 bit, you know, they felt that they were above the - the workers there. But that was in - in those days, things have changed now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Then you told me about the churchgoing people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, they were - they were a little of - you know - big nobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were church people different from chapel people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes. They are aren't they? They're a lot narrower than chapel people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Was there anything else about the church people that differentiated them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - well there was the ministers - long 
ago, you know, some of them wanted attention they wanted more attention than they do today. And you'd respect them too and look up to them, and you'd think they were of a high status. But that was in those days. I mean if you were a minister, yes, that's 
how you were seen. And when the ministers used to come - to - have tea with us, you know, you had to behave yourself and watch what you said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What sort of people would you say went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh very - sociable people, people who mixed easily. Ev
erybody went. I mean there wasn't anything else that would, you know - occupy somebody's mind except the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about the church people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well they were on their own all the time. They didn't mix. Not very much. And I remember some husba
nds going to the church and others going to the chapel. Oh there was a lot of that long ago. They didn't all turn you know, all - change with their husbands that is. I mean some went on going to church and the others to the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Would you say that the ordinary people in the area where you lived had the same standard of living, were they all the same?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - well they were all the same level.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 There weren't different groups within the ordinary people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, there weren't. There weren't. Not in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 There weren't any workers who felt themselves to be superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well - I mean there were people who were aristocratic in those days. You mean amongst the workers? Yes, amongst the workers as well.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember any of these aristocratic families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, I remember a few to - that - you know, over towards Traws.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What sort of families were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well they were sort of people that - well after you'd approached them they were O.K. But they were
 very difficult, some of them, to approach. And others were - well you could sort of go to their world, and do everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Why do you think that they felt they were better than other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well - I mean, the things was it was a different natu
re. And they'd been - brought up in a different way, because it all depends on how you've been brought up you see, doesn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You don't think it was because they had some sort of craft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well there was that. I mean, if they'd been to college 
and had schooling, and then of course they felt they were better than anyone. Because I mean ordinary people hadn't had any education, or not very much anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 When you talk of these aristocratic people you do mean workers don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well they had a job. But - they didn't really work very much. In fact it was workers that worked, and they did work in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were there some workers who felt that they were superior to others, was there a distinction between craftsmen an ordinary labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh - well that's a fact. I mean craftsmen - yes, they are - craftsmen, they are - in fact they think they know everything. But then of course they were very good craftsmen in lots of things. But - you know - not so much as there are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember some families being called rough and others respectable?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh yes. There were some who were very rough. And they were just out for all they could get for themselves. And the respectable ones, well they were better. Those people could s
hare, and you could go to - approach those people and ask for - things. But - you couldn't go to the - to the - the mean ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you think your mother and father had the same attitudes to people of different groups or classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh they were the same with everyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And your mother and father agreed on certain attitudes did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh yes, all the time they did. Because you see, neither of them had had any schooling, therefore they couldn't really ponder upon anything that - wasn't to do with their own work, and their own pleasures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember thinking that your mother felt herself to belong to a particular group or class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, no, nothing like that. Because - they only had a very - light life. There was nothing deep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did she feel the same as her neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, everyone was the same level. In the Sunday school and everywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember if it was possible in those days to move from one group to another group, to move up to a higher status?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well 
no, they didn't because, I mean, I must say that - while they were on this earth they had a very happy life. A life that didn't really change very much until the war came. Very quiet. And very happy, with no bad thoughts of anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember if any of your neighbours or friends managed to improve themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, I do. And specially after the war, because }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 they\rquote d}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  seen and they'd had more schooling and they could go from school to college. There were more opportunities then, but I mean, yo
u know, there were no opportunities when - when mother and father were small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember anyone in particular who did improve himself after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well I don't know, I can't remember. But several have done it. After they've seen - more of
 life, and some people - bettered themselves for the better as it were. But other people, I mean, sort of improved themselves to their own detriment. They'd seen too much. They'd had too much of everything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember anyone being called a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, there were - several of those in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Why was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well it was because their nature was so kind. And they were so happy with everyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember seeing a policeman around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh ye
s, I do. Good Lord, yes. And I was frightened of the bugger. I remember you know when we were in Cae Iago, I remember my father - we could see the policeman coming down the hill you see, and if there was anything bad going on, oh, we were terrified. I rea
lly hated to see him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 If you were bad do you ever remember your mother saying, I'll go for the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, she did that. Watch out for the policeman, she'd say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How did the policeman treat people in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - in those day
s he was pretty cruel. They had no sympathy then. No, none at all. Of course it's changed now. In a way it's a pity they weren't more like they were now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, it wasn't, my father bought Cae Iago. And of course when he was i
n Bryn Rhyd well he got - that house from my grandfather. It was a small house you see and my grandfather had built a bigger house for them, and so we lived in the little house until we came to Cae Iago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 So you didn't have a landlord or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. We didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you ever remember feeling that your parents had difficulty in making ends meet, to keep things going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh it's been very hard. They had to be very careful about how to live and not to spend, and we couldn't have anything new u
nless - there was money to pay for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Now did you feel towards this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh well we'd been brought up to it you see. We didn't know what spending was. You'd been pickled in it so - you didn't expect anything else. You know, you just sort of kept to the same society or community.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you know if it made any difference when your father was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, it did. And nothing came in at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You didn't get charity from the parish at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No we didn't. I mean the world - the world's changed a lot and improved a lot since then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You said you never had the charity at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, we didn't. Luckily we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 If there was someone in your area who people disapproved of very strongly was there some particular way of showing this disapproval?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh yes, I mean in those days they were very straight forward, they just said things to your face. But then other people were - the other way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You don't remember people going to the houses of the people they disapproved of and making a very loud noise outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
No. No, there wasn't that in those days. No, it was a very good time. I mean, the only thing that there was in those days was the odd tramp. And of course in those days everyone was afraid of him, and they'd take ma
tches and things away from him. But they'd give him food and a place to stay - to sleep in buildings. And some were very gentlemanly and others were the other way. And then the workers too like the - the workers on the road, they were fantastic with the c
hildren, and they'd share their food with the children and then of course the children would want to take food to the roadman, and of course the children thought the world of being allowed to eat with the roadm}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 n.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And the roadmen moved around working on different roads did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 Well}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
l yes, they did, because - I remember a man had to break up a whole mound of stone and he - he had to do it with a hammer and he sat there for days, breaking these, in order to put them on the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 But did he have a home to go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, yes, he came from Gellilydan, you know, in the parish of Maentwrog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Do you ever remember people making effigies, like straw men, to symbolize the person they disapproved of? And marching it along through the streets or something?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, there was very little of that in those days. I mean everyone was happy. People were happy with their lives. In their world.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember any customs like gathering money by wishing people a Happy New Year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh yes, we did. And I remember once an old farmer saying - you know, we - we hadn't gone one year - we - we'd sort of given up collecting in this way and this farmer said to us you know that it was a great shame that th
ese sort of customs should have - should be kept up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember any other customs like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Well - I remember we used to go to school on the day of the fair, we were allowed to wear a - a white apron and a white dress, this was in the - th
e April fair. But then - we never had anything like a Christmas tree. We didn't know what a Christmas tree was. We'd never seen one. And we never had anything in our stockings either. Oh no, we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you hang them up though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, I remembe
r - myself hanging them up, and I only got an orange - and some black; sweets. And I never put it up again. 'Cos I knew I wouldn't get anything. But of course it's altered now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember having lessons with your parents or from a private tutor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
No, we didn't. No, we had to fight ourselves. They didn't have time for us. But remember there were some who did get that sort of coaching, I mean people who could afford it, but we never did as a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh I was five. And it was quite a way to walk to. through the woods.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What time in the morning did you leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh we had to leave before half past eight, but I was never late for school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What time did you come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well, in those days it was half past three to four.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you always go to afternoon school once you'd started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, once we started we went to school all through the day. Once we were five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 It was a primary school wasn't it? And girls and boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, mixed. And then in those days you had to be - thirteen or fourteen before you could go to Blaenau school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you go to Balenau school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No I didn't. No, I had to stay at home to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you walk to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes. In every weather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How long did it take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh it took over half an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh, with a crowd. There was a crowd going to school, and then on other occasions there wouldn't be so many. Oh yes, I mean everyone together }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  know, we all went together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And you took your food to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Yes, that's right, we took it with us. And there was this old black stove and you used to put your - bread and butter to warm on there. It was black - blacklead it was, nothing like they are today. And it has improved for the better hasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you like school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Yes. Oh I liked school, I liked the teachers. I was never slapped, and I was never late for school. I mean - I had to - be allowed to go and I - in order to be punctual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember the teachers emphasizing certain things as being important in life, like manners or tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, we were taught that. And being punctual. Oh yes. And you see, if you had been a good girl all through the week then you wer
e allowed to go on top of the seat so that - every - all the other children could see you. That was if you'd been a good girl all the week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did they emphasise ways of speaking at all? Did they want you to speak pure Welsh or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
No, no, not at all. I mean I didn't even learn English at school. No, I didn't, only - only compositions. We got, you know, essays to write - in English. But I man as far as talking goes I never spoke it. No, I never spoke English.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You said you were never punished by the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No I wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about other children, were they punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, they did and they deserved it if they'd done - mischievous things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What sort of things happened to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh they were caned or 
they had to stay behind. And they had to write lines for about quarter of an hour or half an hour, and that was a great prison that, imprisonment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did girls - and boys have the same punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, they did. Exactly the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 For what sort of things were they punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh well if you'd been fighting, say if you'd hit one of the children with a stone, or if you'd sworn or something, then you got punished. In fact you were punished for everything, if you'd done anything out of place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did they ask you what you'd done at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did they ever go to see the school or the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. They didn't. They never had any cause to go
, as far as I know, go to - to see the teacher, because if - you know, we hadn't done anything out of place. I mean I don't remember us - I don't remember anything like that happening.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Would you say that the other children in the school came from the same type of home as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, they did, but there were some who came from big families who were - you know, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 pretty}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  poor and pretty dirty. Only everybody was together. And this is another thing we were punished for, if you shouted - after someone
, then you were punished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember the teachers singling out some children for different treatment from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no, I don't. They were very good in those days, there was no distinction made between anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Well there was some that were worse than others, but I never saw any cause for complaint - of a - gang - that was doing - you know - doing bad things. They didn't, you know, destroy things because, you know, they couldn't really
 because the policeman would have been after you in those days, and so you couldn't or you would get a terrible punishment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember groups of children getting together to do something, to play something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, I mean we used to play to
gether - in the old days - we used to like to play little trains, and there'd be a whole crowd of us with that, and another lot playing ball, and others playing tiddlywinks made with - out of buttons, and we'd play - with a pole and we'd play skipping.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember some children being left out of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no, very little. No, they'd be pushed forward to get the advantage of everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You didn't go to another school after this one did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. Except I - only - Trawsfynydd sc
hool and Llan school, once I'd come to live in Cae Iago that is. I was eleven when I went to Llan school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you feel there was any great change going to Llan school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well I prefer - preferred Trawsfynydd school. And the people of Traws were mo
re united. But then I mean we became very friendly with Llan but - you know, the headmaster's nature was different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What time did you set out to school from Llan, to go to Llan school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well, quarter past to half past eight - the same. In order to get there on time, to be there early in fact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 It was the same type of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What did you feel for the teachers in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh well I was very homesick for Traws. I remember I cried for a week, refusing to go to Llan sc
hool, because I missed my teachers and missed my friends. And I missed - well - the teaching wasn't the same. The lessons weren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did they emphasise different things at this school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, they did, they weren't the same - outlook on everything. But I came to like it well enough, after about two weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did they punish more or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well I can't say - I'm sure they did - punish a bit more in Llan. The headmaster wasn't of the same nature.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did they get the same type of punishment, the can and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, they were caned.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 For the same type of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, yes, the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your parents still show interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And were the children in Llan the same type of homes as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes they were. The - the majority of them that is. But there were some remember there were some you know who -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You mean poorer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, and - and others that were - you know, richer. You see, it depends entirely on your natur
e how you're able to do - how you're able to manage with - with these different people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember favouritism in Llan school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, there were favourites, specially if you were going to go on to Balenau school and then there were
 favourites. There wasn't a sort of - feeling of community all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember gangs or groups in Llan school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well, yes, there was a gang of boys - boys from the farm, and they were very strong boys, and they used to do lots of bad th
ings, and they'd prevent you from going home and then there'd be a big row. They'd want a kiss or something from you and you see some of them went up - towards Bala and others towards Cwm Cynfal and then you see we were always in trouble over that. Yes, }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 especially}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  as we got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember some children being left out of things in Llan school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, not much like that. Not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh I was fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Would you have stayed if you'd have had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh yes I would. I'd give the world to go back. To go back to school. I so liked school. But I had to come home to work with my mother and to bring up the other children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you ever go to night school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, there wasn't anything like that. But I think the world of things like the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 Women\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
 Institute and I've kept up with that, you know, ever since - well I joined just after I was fourteen, that was when you could join then. I really thing the world of that, I've learnt an eno
rmous amount with them. But we never had the opportunity to go to night school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Have you regretted anything about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, I haven't regretted anything. Because I helped my mother. And you see in one way it was a - a loss to me to los
e my education, but then I've benefited from - from bringing up the children with my mother. And that's - that was my calling. I had to do it. But by today of course it's a great loss to someone, but I just put it out of my mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you think you benefited from going to school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, school - it did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 While you were at school did you have a part time job at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no. I only had school and then I worked at home. And of course I - I worked - when I went home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 But you never went out to work anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you stay at home with your mother and father until you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, I did go to work with an auntie in Llandudno for about two summers, keeping visitors, and I think I learnt more there than I ever did.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How old were you when you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh I wasn't twenty. Eighteen or something like that, and I went for two summers. But apart from that I was at home. And I had to kill - slaughter the animals with my father. And I remember - in the time of the 
war when there was a blackout we used to have to kill at night, because - and he was terribly busy in those days because the boys were away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you go to Llandudno after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And apart from that you were always home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Yes, that's right. And I remember - if someone in the community was ill then my father and me, we would have to rush to them to - to give them help. Even if you were ill yourself you had to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What exactly were your duties at home, you've already talked about doing the house-work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, I had to do the house - you know, cleaning and washing up. And then had to work outside, attending to the animals if there were any.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh I used to work all day. I didn't have many - much - relief at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You didn't work Sundays did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you ever have a half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no, I never had a half day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And you didn't have holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes. We did get m
oney. And it was taken to the Post Office. I mean what we did get, that's what happened to it. And then I got the - the - money from the eggs, but had to buy - clothes out of that. Because we used to, you know, ask my father all the time, oh I want some n
ew clothes. And he'd just say, wait. You wait. I think we'd still be waiting if we hadn't gone to get them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you feel that the money you got was fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, for that time it was. I was - pleased with every sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And you saved all of it did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You didn't spend it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, very little. We spent very little indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How did you feel about working for your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well I did it - well I did it as a calling. I mean there was no choice, you had to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did they treat you fairly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, champion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How did you feel towards the work, did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, yes, I did. I mean I had to like it or - well we had to. In fact I like all work. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 It doesn't matter to me what I'm doing, it didn't matter what there was to do, I used to try my best.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Since the first world war you stayed at home until you married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, that's right, until I married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Then after you married you worked on the farm did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes. I worked on a farm. And I worked very hard there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How old were you when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh - thirty-four or something, at least that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Would you have preferred to do something else with your life - how did you come to be running a shop, did you 
come here after you left the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Yes, that's right. I came here seven years ago. You know, that's when I came from the animals. And I've given my time to - the shop and I like it. I like mixing with people, and doing the best that I can. I really enjoy it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Would you have preferred to do another job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well if it wasn't for the shop - I would have become a home help or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Would you have preferred to have done a different job to staying at home with your parents in your early life, do you regret anything?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
No, I don't regret anything. Anything I've tried to do. I mean I - it was of interest to me just to work. And if it wasn't for having this job here well I would have become a home help or - you know - going round old people
, to see if they needed any messages or else I'd do babysitting, if somebody wanted to go out in the evening. I can't be still you know. I mean I don't regret anything. I would have liked to have been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 able}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  o go on but - doesn't worry me at all 'cos I did what I could for my mother and father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You didn't serve an apprenticeship or training period did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, no, I didn't. No, I never had the opportunity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you ever belong to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No, I didn't nothing like that. I only paid insurance - in order to get my pension.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Would you say that workers and employers }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 see}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  the world in the same sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No they don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What's the difference then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh I don't know. There are just so many different ideas and attitudes.
 Because - the worker needs to be - honest, and - the - and the employer tries to explain the meaning of lots of things to the worker, but he often doesn't understand, or refuses to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Would you say that there was a division of interest amongst workers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh well, workers, they get all sorts of opportunities today. But there wasn't anything before. But I mean now they get - all sorts of opportunities. They get night school and everything. They even go to college, you can go to college and do a
 course. I'd like to go myself but I'm too old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you feel that the distinction between craftsmen and other workers is important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, that's very important. According to my judgement anyway. I mean the craftsmen has given his life for years
 with very little - earnings, but I mean the worker, he just gets his money and can do what he likes with it. No, but craftsmen - I believe in craftsmen myself and - you have to be a craftsman in fact to do satisfying work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Would you say that working has changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Well yes, yes, definitely, because for us work has been - within the family. And it's brought a lot of pleasure, and money. It's brought us a good life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did leaving school change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No it didn't at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. I did my best to everything and to the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you spend Sundays differently after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well, yes, because as we
 grew up we realized that we had to read, in order to be, you know, in the same society as other people. Yes, we changed quite a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And you started to do things on Sunday did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, we started to work more on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 But you still went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh yes, we did. Yes, we kept doing that, but we just used to do these other things on the sly without anyone knowing because they didn't think that we were reading the newspaper or anything. But you had to as you grew up, otherwise you'd 
lose out on everything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. No never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You didn't vote or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No. Well I mean my mother and father were Liberal so I was a Liberal too. But I didn't know what it - what it meant, I didn't kn
ow what sort of - attitudes were related to that sort of politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You don't remember voting after women got the vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, I remember going to vote. Oh and I thought the world of myself too, got half day in order to go and vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember when you first voted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No I don't, I don't remember. But it must have been what - about forty years ago, or maybe it was more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Do you remember feeling that you were under any pressure from anyone to vote for any particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 N
o, I wasn't, I didn't take any notice of anything. I mean, I say - everything and everybody should have their part in life, and I don't think politics should come into your life at all, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 
especially}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  if you're in any sort of business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You never belonged to a political party then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 And you never worked for any party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 No I didn't. Except helping every party. It's never good for people to know which party you belong to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you start spending your free time in a different way after you left school, did you go out more in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh yes, I went out more, I was allowed to go out more. Because the freedom had come more by then. We were allowed to go to the pictures and we could go to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 Llano}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  on a Saturday night. Then of course we had to be home by - you know - this time or that time. But you know, we didn't go very much. Maybe to a concert or something sometimes, or to an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 eisteddfod}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 .
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh with friends and relatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you make new friends with boys or girls at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, I was friend with a lot and - great friends with some and none with others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 How did you meet your new friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Well they would come to our home, and then there were workers, farm workers and
 they'd be working with different things. And we'd become friends with them. In fact we were friends with a lot of the workers, Englishmen and everything, and my father was very kind to them. They'd often have tea in Cae Iago. You know, like the electrici
t
y workers who were putting up these old poles you know, around about the place. And there was a big crowd of them and they'd come and - have tea all the time. We had to respect everybody. And if they were English, you see my father couldn't speak English 
at all, he'd just beckon to them to come into the house to have a cup of tea in the house. I mean he couldn't actually say it. Come for a cup of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 So you didn't speak English then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh no, very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh yes, I had very great friend, well sometimes it was with relatives and sometimes you know people who didn't relate to you at all. And then of course we used to fight as well. I remember four of us that used to be in Llan school, and by t
his time we had left, and there were two of us and two others and we'd fought and we wouldn't speak to each other and I sort of - called a truce and we became friends again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You said you went to pictures and concerts with your friends, where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh to Blaenau.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you do anything else with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
No, very little. But the only thing we did do was go to the - society at the chapel, you know, after we'd passed fourteen. And then there was a drama group and we used to belong to that
. I used to like drama. But I mean for singing and things a I was hopeless.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Your parents met your friends of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did they expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, they did, and who we were going with too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did they expect you to be home at a particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh yes, they did, we had to be home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did you have any children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes. One boy. He's a lecturer in Salford. In the university there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 So he went to college did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, he went to Aber
ystwyth and he was there for six years, and then he went to Oxford for two years, and then he went to St - St - Sir John Cass in London as a lecturer and then he went to Salford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What does he lecture in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh chemistry. In fact he's a senior lecturer now. And he's got two boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about your brothers, what did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 You mean which work? Oh they were all butchers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Every one of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Teddy became a butcher and he went to Llandudno very early on and Griffith went then as a b
utcher and he died in Llandudno, and then Evan, he's dead now. And he was a butcher too. And now Howell's a butcher. Here. He's a butcher. And my youngest brother John, well he's a farmer. Oh he's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12005850\charrsid401146 able}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146  to - slaughter and everything, and he used to slaughte
r when he was very young, but he's a farmer now, he's got two farms over in - Anglesey. And - that's five isn't it? Yes, because Bob had died, he was a farmer too. He had to go and work on a farm. In fact he was a farm worker, because - his health was - w
asn't very good. And my sister, well she had every opportunity to go on but she didn't do the things that she should have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What did her husband do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh he was a farmer too.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 That's what he did all his life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Did your brothers have their own butcher business, they didn't work for other butchers did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh no, they didn't. Well Teddy and Howell had their own businesses anyway. But Griffith was a director of a firm in Llandudno. And then Evan, he got his own business to - in Cwn Penmachno.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 What about your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 Oh he's been a farmer all his life. And he had the opportunity to go ahead but he liked being at home. He was a very good sheep farmer.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15685967 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 When did your brother and sister that died, when did they die?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7275719 GJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6446688\charrsid401146 
Oh well - my sister was - quite young, she must have been about eight. And my brother - well - he'd started working when he was fourteen, on the farms, he must have been - sixteen or so.
\par }}